here is the pasted Wikipedia page: Gryllus texensis is a species of field cricket originally identified by William H. Cade and Otte in the early 2000s. Cade and Otte clarify that field crickets collected in the Southeastern United States from Florida to Texas identified as Gryllus integer, were in fact misidentified, and should have been classified as G. texensis. Morphologically, Cade and Otte found no differences between G. texensis and Gryllus rubens, however, their call song structure was significantly different.
